  <title>Gio.Menu</title>
  <synopsis><code>
const Gio = imports.gi.Gio;

let menu = new Gio.Menu();
  </code></synopsis>
  <p><link xref="Gio.Menu"/> is a simple implementation of <link xref="Gio.MenuModel"/>.
You populate a <link xref="Gio.Menu"/> by adding <link xref="Gio.MenuItem"/> instances to it.</p>  <p>There are some convenience functions to allow you to directly
add items (avoiding <link xref="Gio.MenuItem"/>) for the common cases. To add
a regular item, use <link xref="Gio.insert"/>. To add a section, use
<link xref="Gio.insert_section"/>. To add a submenu, use
<link xref="Gio.insert_submenu"/>.</p>
  <p>Since 2.32</p>
